What is outside,
no one will ever know.

1135
00:54:05,188 --> 00:54:06,258
Honey?

1136
00:54:06,323 --> 00:54:07,893
Yeah?

1137
00:54:07,958 --> 00:54:10,438
I'm going out,
and I'll be back later.

1138
00:54:10,494 --> 00:54:12,371
Are you all right?

1139
00:54:12,429 --> 00:54:14,067
Yeah. Where are you going?

1140
00:54:14,131 --> 00:54:17,078
I have some shopping
and things to do.

1141
00:54:17,134 --> 00:54:19,580
Oh, look at this!

1142
00:54:19,636 --> 00:54:22,082
This is beautiful.

1143
00:54:22,139 --> 00:54:24,176
Oh, you never saw one before?

1144
00:54:24,241 --> 00:54:26,915
Only in the store.
My goodness, look what they've done.

1145
00:54:26,977 --> 00:54:28,422
Did you ever use one?

1146
00:54:28,478 --> 00:54:29,513
No.

1147
00:54:29,579 --> 00:54:31,081
Do you know how to type?

1148
00:54:31,148 --> 00:54:32,593
Do I know how to type?

1149
00:54:32,649 --> 00:54:34,595
I was the fastest typist
in my class.

1150
00:54:34,651 --> 00:54:35,595
Number one.

1151
00:54:35,652 --> 00:54:36,790
But it was manual.

1152
00:54:36,853 --> 00:54:38,526
Then they didn't
do all those things.

1153
00:54:38,588 --> 00:54:40,124
Come on.
You got to try it.

1154
00:54:40,190 --> 00:54:41,760
Oh, no, I couldn't do that.

1155
00:54:41,825 --> 00:54:43,270
No. Try it. It's easy.

1156
00:54:43,326 --> 00:54:44,862
It's the same as manual.

1157
00:54:44,928 --> 00:54:46,771
It just does it all for you.

1158
00:54:46,830 --> 00:54:48,070
Let's see.

1159
00:54:54,671 --> 00:54:56,014
Mother!

1160
00:55:00,744 --> 00:55:02,485
You're amazing!

1161
00:55:02,546 --> 00:55:06,119
No mistakes, and you're fast.

1162
00:55:06,183 --> 00:55:08,493
I'm impressed.

1163
00:55:08,552 --> 00:55:11,192
I never knew this.

1164
00:55:11,254 --> 00:55:14,258
Your mother does a lot of things
you don't know.

1165
00:55:14,324 --> 00:55:15,860
Well, that's why I'm here.

1166
00:55:15,926 --> 00:55:17,564
Tell me everything.

1167
00:55:17,627 --> 00:55:19,732
You came here
to find out what I do?

1168
00:55:19,796 --> 00:55:21,332
I thought you came here because

1169
00:55:21,398 --> 00:55:22,968
of the problems with the women.

1170
00:55:23,033 --> 00:55:24,535
The problems with the women,

1171
00:55:24,601 --> 00:55:27,172
to find out what you do--
the whole thing. Come on.

1172
00:55:27,237 --> 00:55:28,841
Not now, dear. I have to go.

1173
00:55:28,905 --> 00:55:31,078
Oh, Mother?

1174
00:55:31,141 --> 00:55:34,350
I'm taking you out to dinner tonight,
so be ready at 8:00.

1175
00:55:34,411 --> 00:55:35,754
What?

1176
00:55:35,812 --> 00:55:36,813
We have a date.

1177
00:55:36,880 --> 00:55:38,518
I want you to be ready
at 8:00 sharp.

1178
00:55:38,582 --> 00:55:39,890
I'll pick you up in your room.

1179
00:55:39,950 --> 00:55:42,055
Honey, you don't have to do that.
I'll make something.

1180
00:55:42,119 --> 00:55:43,757
No more house cheese.

1181
00:55:43,820 --> 00:55:46,460
This is going to be
a very special evening.

1182
00:55:46,523 --> 00:55:47,467
Hmm!

1183
00:56:11,648 --> 00:56:13,787
To the experiment,
whatever it is.

1184
00:56:13,850 --> 00:56:15,761
To the experiment.

1185
00:56:23,960 --> 00:56:25,530
And you look good.

1186
00:56:26,930 --> 00:56:28,409
But?

1187
00:56:28,465 --> 00:56:30,308
What, dear?

1188
00:56:30,367 --> 00:56:32,074
Just wondering
when the but's coming.

1189
00:56:32,135 --> 00:56:33,739
Is that what you think I do?

1190
00:56:33,804 --> 00:56:35,579
I don't think you do it.
That's what you do.

1191
00:56:35,639 --> 00:56:37,084
I don't mean anything by it.

1192
00:56:37,140 --> 00:56:38,585
It's just something
a mother does.

1193
00:56:38,642 --> 00:56:40,417
I don't know that
every mother does that.

1194
00:56:40,477 --> 00:56:42,252
I don't think
every mother says,

1195
00:56:42,312 --> 00:56:44,883
"Honey, you look good,
but your hair is thinning."

1196
00:56:44,948 --> 00:56:47,394
Honey, I never told you
your hair was thinning.

1197
00:56:47,450 --> 00:56:48,588
Yes, you did.

1198
00:56:48,652 --> 00:56:50,757
The last time
I was at the house,

1199
00:56:50,821 --> 00:56:52,858
on my way out
you called after me,

1200
00:56:52,923 --> 00:56:55,096
"Look out for your bald spot."
Remember?

1201
00:56:55,158 --> 00:56:57,764
Well, someone has to say that.

1202
00:56:57,828 --> 00:57:01,833
And by the way, whatever you did,
it looks wonderful.

1203
00:57:01,898 --> 00:57:03,104
You can barely tell.

1204
00:57:03,166 --> 00:57:04,770
I used that Minoxidil stuff.

1205
00:57:04,835 --> 00:57:06,178
I was one of the lucky ones.

1206
00:57:06,236 --> 00:57:09,046
But it doesn't work up here, hmm?

1207
00:57:09,105 --> 00:57:10,550
What are you-- What is--Why?

1208
00:57:10,607 --> 00:57:12,109
Why should it work up here?

1209
00:57:12,175 --> 00:57:14,587
I have hair here.
I didn't even put it here.

1210
00:57:14,644 --> 00:57:15,714
I see there's hair there.

1211
00:57:15,779 --> 00:57:17,053
No, no, dear. I was just--

1212
00:57:17,113 --> 00:57:18,615
It's for the back.

1213
00:57:18,682 --> 00:57:20,628
That's where I put it.
That's where it worked.

1214
00:57:20,684 --> 00:57:22,630
Oh, that's a miracle.

1215
00:57:22,686 --> 00:57:24,427
Just think.

1216
00:57:24,487 --> 00:57:25,989
It was a blood pressure medicine.

1217
00:57:26,056 --> 00:57:27,558
Isn't that funny?

1218
00:57:27,624 --> 00:57:30,070
They accidentally
found out it grew hair.

1219
00:57:30,126 --> 00:57:32,572
Isn't that the way
it always works?

1220
00:57:32,629 --> 00:57:36,076
They always accidentally
find something.

1221
00:57:36,132 --> 00:57:38,738
Do you know how the cane
was invented?

1222
00:57:38,802 --> 00:57:40,247
No.

1223
00:57:46,509 --> 00:57:47,544
How?

1224
00:57:47,611 --> 00:57:50,251
Oh, I don't know, dear.

1225
00:57:50,313 --> 00:57:53,522
I just can't imagine
that was its original purpose.

1226
00:57:58,488 --> 00:57:59,865
Thank you.

1227
00:57:59,923 --> 00:58:01,095
That looks delicious.

1228
00:58:01,157 --> 00:58:02,465
Looks lovely.

1229
00:58:02,525 --> 00:58:03,731
And you, sir.

1230
00:58:03,793 --> 00:58:05,397
Thank you very much.

1231
00:58:05,462 --> 00:58:07,533
Would you like another martini?

1232
00:58:07,597 --> 00:58:08,803
Oh, no.

1233
00:58:08,865 --> 00:58:11,141
Yes. 2 olives.

1234
00:58:14,271 --> 00:58:16,114
I'm fine. Thank you.

1235
00:58:20,277 --> 00:58:23,019
You don't speak to your brother
very much, do you, dear?

1236
00:58:23,079 --> 00:58:25,059
No. No, I don't.

1237
00:58:25,115 --> 00:58:26,423
I wonder why.

1238
00:58:26,483 --> 00:58:28,258
Maybe it's the age difference.

1239
00:58:28,318 --> 00:58:30,059
Well, age difference,
every difference.

1240
00:58:30,120 --> 00:58:32,623
You know, we're just different.
That's all.

1241
00:58:32,689 --> 00:58:36,068
I just wish you could meet
a girl like Cheryl.

1242
00:58:36,126 --> 00:58:38,572
She's a wonderful girl,
don't you think?

1243
00:58:38,628 --> 00:58:40,733
I like her.
Yeah, she's very nice.

1244
00:58:40,797 --> 00:58:42,105
So what happened?

1245
00:58:42,165 --> 00:58:44,736
You just had some bad luck?

1246
00:58:44,801 --> 00:58:46,178
What do you mean?

1247
00:58:46,236 --> 00:58:48,716
I just mean, he seemed
to hit it off right away,

1248
00:58:48,772 --> 00:58:52,276
and they have children, and they're
happy, and you haven't found it.

1249
00:58:52,342 --> 00:58:54,117
Well, I can't help that, Mother.

1250
00:58:54,177 --> 00:58:56,623
I can't help who I am.
What am I supposed to do?

1251
00:58:56,680 --> 00:58:58,626
Of course not, dear.
I know that.

1252
00:58:58,682 --> 00:59:01,424
I'm just saying it's interesting
how someone has good luck

1253
00:59:01,484 --> 00:59:03,225
and someone has bad luck.

1254
00:59:03,286 --> 00:59:07,098
Mother, I don't look at my life
as good luck and bad luck, you know?

1255
00:59:07,157 --> 00:59:09,865
I'm on a quest.
We're different people.

1256
00:59:09,926 --> 00:59:12,532
He's an agent.
I'm a writer.

1257
00:59:12,595 --> 00:59:15,007
There's a big difference there.

1258
00:59:15,065 --> 00:59:16,544
You know something?

1259
00:59:16,599 --> 00:59:19,045
Maybe you should write
about that.

1260
00:59:19,102 --> 00:59:20,547
What did you say?

1261
00:59:20,603 --> 00:59:22,605
I just think you
should think about

1262
00:59:22,672 --> 00:59:24,709
writing about real
things--you know,

1263
00:59:24,774 --> 00:59:27,550
people, instead of all that
science fiction all the time.

1264
00:59:27,610 --> 00:59:29,453
Science fiction has people in it.

1265
00:59:29,512 --> 00:59:31,389
What kind of a comment is that?

1266
00:59:31,448 --> 00:59:33,121
It's not a bad comment, dear.

1267
00:59:33,183 --> 00:59:34,526
It's just my opinion.

1268
00:59:34,584 --> 00:59:36,723
I mean, I just think
it would be interesting

1269
00:59:36,786 --> 00:59:38,788
to write about
what's really right here

1270
00:59:38,855 --> 00:59:40,892
instead of all
that made-up stuff--

1271
00:59:40,957 --> 00:59:42,561
you know,
with the large heads.

1272
00:59:42,625 --> 00:59:46,163
And what was that one character
you had with just a big hand?

1273
00:59:46,229 --> 00:59:48,231
Even if I wrote
about "right here,"

1274
00:59:48,298 --> 00:59:50,539
I'd have to make it up,
wouldn't I?

1275
00:59:50,600 --> 00:59:54,241
Isn't it more visionary to make up
a world that doesn't even exist?

1276
00:59:54,304 --> 00:59:55,282
Maybe.

1277
00:59:55,338 --> 00:59:57,784
Well, maybe you're right.
You're right.

1278
00:59:57,841 --> 01:00:00,082
Mother, you don't have to
like science fiction.

1279
01:00:00,143 --> 01:00:02,749
I'm not going to bully you
into liking the genre.

1280
01:00:02,812 --> 01:00:04,519
No, dear,
I love science fiction.

1281
01:00:04,581 --> 01:00:06,083
No, you don't.

1282
01:00:06,149 --> 01:00:08,857
Oh, yes, I do.
I think it's very creative.

1283
01:00:08,918 --> 01:00:12,764
But not as creative as, what--
a story about brothers?

1284
01:00:15,358 --> 01:00:17,338
You know, dear,
you misunderstand me.

1285
01:00:17,394 --> 01:00:20,000
I know. Vice versa.

1286
01:00:25,201 --> 01:00:26,874
Well, let's change the subject.

1287
01:00:26,936 --> 01:00:28,506
To a new subject.

1288
01:00:28,571 --> 01:00:29,743
New subject.

1289
01:00:35,145 --> 01:00:37,386
Maybe when you
stopped eating meat,

1290
01:00:37,447 --> 01:00:39,586
your writing became
a little thinner.

1291
01:00:46,289 --> 01:00:47,563
Oh, dear, the phone.

1292
01:00:47,624 --> 01:00:49,570
Why don't you get
an answering machine?

1293
01:00:49,626 --> 01:00:52,232
I had one, but it broke.
I never got it fixed.

1294
01:00:52,295 --> 01:00:54,366
You don't get them fixed.
You throw them away.

1295
01:00:54,431 --> 01:00:55,409
Hello?

1296
01:00:55,465 --> 01:00:56,443
Hi, Mom.

1297
01:00:56,499 --> 01:00:57,603
Oh, hi, honey.

1298
01:00:57,667 --> 01:00:59,340
Sit down in front
of the camera.

1299
01:00:59,402 --> 01:01:02,076
Honey, I just walked in.
I'm exhausted.

1300
01:01:02,138 --> 01:01:04,618
Let me use this phone.

1301
01:01:04,674 --> 01:01:06,745
Where were you?

1302
01:01:06,810 --> 01:01:08,949
We went to
the most beautiful restaurant.

1303
01:01:09,012 --> 01:01:11,720
Listen, I closed
a giant deal today.

1304
01:01:11,781 --> 01:01:13,260
Big deal.

1305
01:01:13,316 --> 01:01:15,023
Oh, really, dear?

1306
01:01:15,085 --> 01:01:18,032
It was fabulous.
It was fabulous!

1307
01:01:18,088 --> 01:01:20,864
I'll call you later, and you
can tell me all about it.

1308
01:01:20,924 --> 01:01:23,268
Let me tell you about it now.
You can't talk now?

1309
01:01:23,326 --> 01:01:24,771
Honey, I just walked in,

1310
01:01:24,828 --> 01:01:27,866
and I just--well, I'd like
to be able to concentrate.

1311
01:01:27,931 --> 01:01:30,036
OK. Forget it.
I'll tell you about it later.

1312
01:01:30,100 --> 01:01:31,545
All right, dear.
Sleep well.

1313
01:01:31,601 --> 01:01:33,046
Good. Say hi to John.

1314
01:01:33,103 --> 01:01:34,548
All right.

1315
01:01:34,604 --> 01:01:35,674
OK. Bye.

1316
01:01:37,140 --> 01:01:39,381
Your brother says hi.

1317
01:01:39,442 --> 01:01:40,716
Hi.

1318
01:01:40,777 --> 01:01:42,916
Want something to eat?

1319
01:01:42,979 --> 01:01:44,549
You got to be kidding.

1320
01:01:44,614 --> 01:01:46,059
You're not full?

1321
01:01:46,116 --> 01:01:49,461
What a wonderful time we had
this evening. Thank you, honey.

1322
01:01:49,519 --> 01:01:51,055
It was fun.

1323
01:01:51,121 --> 01:01:54,568
As much as I don't want to,
I guess I'll go in my room

1324
01:01:54,624 --> 01:01:57,400
and see if I can work
a little bit.

1325
01:01:57,460 --> 01:01:59,565
You don't feel silly
in that room, huh, dear?

1326
01:01:59,629 --> 01:02:01,267
I do a little bit, yeah.

1327
01:02:01,331 --> 01:02:03,538
And yet you still want
to be in there.

1328
01:02:03,600 --> 01:02:04,544
Yeah.

1329
01:02:04,601 --> 01:02:06,410
I guess you know
what you're doing.

1330
01:02:06,469 --> 01:02:09,006
So, tomorrow I figure we'll
go shopping and have a nice lunch.

1331
01:02:09,072 --> 01:02:10,710
Oh, I can't do anything tomorrow.

1332
01:02:10,773 --> 01:02:11,717
Why not?

1333
01:02:11,774 --> 01:02:13,276
I have to take the car in.

1334
01:02:13,343 --> 01:02:14,651
What time is that?

1335
01:02:14,711 --> 01:02:15,849
9:00.

1336
01:02:15,912 --> 01:02:18,119
So how does that ruin
the whole day?

1337
01:02:18,181 --> 01:02:19,854
Oh, well, if there's
something wrong,

1338
01:02:19,916 --> 01:02:22,362
you know, they might
want me to leave it.

1339
01:02:22,418 --> 01:02:24,261
You never know what
they're going to say.

1340
01:02:24,320 --> 01:02:26,357
What is wrong with the car?

1341
01:02:26,422 --> 01:02:28,629
It's some sort of a rattle.

1342
01:02:28,691 --> 01:02:30,193
I'll take a look at it.

1343
01:02:30,260 --> 01:02:31,830
No, dear, I can't do that.

1344
01:02:31,895 --> 01:02:32,839
Why not?

1345
01:02:32,896 --> 01:02:34,842
You could void the warranty.

1346
01:02:34,898 --> 01:02:36,002
I could what?

1347
01:02:36,065 --> 01:02:39,046
They told me if I took it
to some other place

1348
01:02:39,102 --> 01:02:41,309
other than the dealer,
it would void the warranty.

1349
01:02:41,371 --> 01:02:42,941
Mother, I'm not another place.
I'm your child.

1350
01:02:43,006 --> 01:02:45,850
I don't have a waiting room
with magazines and a service adviser

1351
01:02:45,909 --> 01:02:48,355
who's going to tap you
on the shoulder and talk to you.

1352
01:02:48,411 --> 01:02:49,515
I'm your kid.

1353
01:02:49,579 --> 01:02:52,958
Honey, forget about it.
You could make it worse.

1354
01:02:59,756 --> 01:03:02,566
I can't get over how much
you know about cars.

1355
01:03:02,625 --> 01:03:04,627
I just tightened the bolt
on the air cleaner.

1356
01:03:04,694 --> 01:03:06,867
I don't really know
anything about cars.

1357
01:03:06,930 --> 01:03:08,068
It's wonderful, dear.

1358
01:03:08,131 --> 01:03:10,077
I'm sure they would
have found something

1359
01:03:10,133 --> 01:03:11,771
to charge me a fortune for.

1360
01:03:11,834 --> 01:03:14,337
It's so nice to have a man
around the house.

1361
01:03:14,404 --> 01:03:16,247
Dad used to fix stuff?

1362
01:03:16,306 --> 01:03:17,512
Oh, God, no.

1363
01:03:17,574 --> 01:03:20,521
I just always liked
that expression.

1364
01:03:31,854 --> 01:03:33,697
<i>Please take the ticket.</i>

1365
01:03:36,859 --> 01:03:38,133
Take that ticket.

1366
01:03:40,163 --> 01:03:41,642
Honey, I wonder--

1367
01:03:41,698 --> 01:03:44,611
Maybe--I don't know,
but we could park the car--

1368
01:03:44,667 --> 01:03:47,375
It's free. You don't even
have to have it validated.

1369
01:03:47,437 --> 01:03:48,780
Just take the ticket.

1370
01:03:48,838 --> 01:03:50,681
You don't have to
have it validated?

1371
01:03:50,740 --> 01:03:54,449
Take the ticket!

1372
01:04:04,621 --> 01:04:07,534
My goodness, look what
they do at these places!

1373
01:04:07,590 --> 01:04:09,069
You've never been here before?

1374
01:04:09,125 --> 01:04:11,071
You know,
it's far from the house.

1375
01:04:11,127 --> 01:04:14,370
What am I going to do?
I'm not going to come here.

1376
01:04:14,430 --> 01:04:16,068
It's 10 minutes from the house.

1377
01:04:16,132 --> 01:04:18,738
Oh. Well, it felt far.

1378
01:04:18,801 --> 01:04:20,371
There's a Gap up there.

1379
01:04:20,436 --> 01:04:22,643
Come on.
I need some underwear.

1380
01:04:29,812 --> 01:04:31,314
Yes, may I help you?

1381
01:04:31,381 --> 01:04:33,418
Yeah, I need to get
some underwear.

1382
01:04:33,483 --> 01:04:34,689
OK.

1383
01:04:34,751 --> 01:04:36,025
That's my son.

1384
01:04:36,085 --> 01:04:38,565
I didn't come here
to pick out underwear for him.

1385
01:04:38,621 --> 01:04:40,760
He's just staying with me
for a while.

1386
01:04:40,823 --> 01:04:42,825
Mother, I understand
when you tell your friends,

1387
01:04:42,892 --> 01:04:45,099
but this is a kid we don't
have to tell this to.

1388
01:04:45,161 --> 01:04:46,435
What is your name?

1389
01:04:46,496 --> 01:04:47,998
Steve.

1390
01:04:48,064 --> 01:04:49,634
Steve,
other than selling us things,

1391
01:04:49,699 --> 01:04:51,906
you don't give a shit
about us, do you?

1392
01:04:53,836 --> 01:04:55,509
No, not really.

1393
01:04:55,571 --> 01:04:57,278
See?

1394
01:04:58,675 --> 01:05:00,120
You tell everyone.

1395
01:05:00,176 --> 01:05:01,484
I don't tell everyone.

1396
01:05:01,544 --> 01:05:03,615
You do.
You don't even realize it.

1397
01:05:03,680 --> 01:05:05,921
You're just trying to justify
everything to strangers.

1398
01:05:05,982 --> 01:05:07,791
That's not it at all, dear.

1399
01:05:07,850 --> 01:05:10,888
People are just curious
why a grown man and his mother

1400
01:05:10,953 --> 01:05:12,557
would be in an underwear store.

1401
01:05:12,622 --> 01:05:14,033
Who cares if they're curious?

1402
01:05:14,090 --> 01:05:15,592
What difference does it make?

1403
01:05:15,658 --> 01:05:17,103
You see what's going on?

1404
01:05:17,160 --> 01:05:19,140
You want their approval,
I want your approval.

1405
01:05:19,195 --> 01:05:20,503
It's all about approval.

1406
01:05:20,563 --> 01:05:22,736
We have an approval problem
in this family.

1407
01:05:22,799 --> 01:05:24,574
We don't have any problem
in this family,

1408
01:05:24,634 --> 01:05:25,977
and lower your voice.

1409
01:05:26,035 --> 01:05:28,072
You're making this
much too serious.

1410
01:05:28,137 --> 01:05:30,549
Now, where do you
want to go next?

1411
01:05:30,606 --> 01:05:32,176
Well, there's a little store

1412
01:05:32,241 --> 01:05:33,948
down there called
"Tell It All."

1413
01:05:34,010 --> 01:05:37,389
You go in and tell them
your most personal secrets.

1414
01:05:37,447 --> 01:05:38,687
You're joking?

1415
01:05:38,748 --> 01:05:40,421
Yeah.

1416
01:05:40,483 --> 01:05:43,089
If only your writing
were that real.

1417
01:05:46,456 --> 01:05:48,766
Oh, look at this.

1418
01:05:48,825 --> 01:05:50,600
Oh!

1419
01:05:50,660 --> 01:05:52,298
Hi!

1420
01:05:52,362 --> 01:05:53,864
Hi, cutie.

1421
01:05:53,930 --> 01:05:55,603
Hi, cutie.

1422
01:05:55,665 --> 01:05:56,905
Yeah.

1423
01:05:56,966 --> 01:05:58,104
Honey, put that down.

1424
01:05:58,167 --> 01:05:59,510
Don't play with that.

1425
01:05:59,569 --> 01:06:01,742
Do you know
how much this dog is?

1426
01:06:01,804 --> 01:06:03,181
Mother, I'm just petting it.

1427
01:06:03,239 --> 01:06:05,276
I'm not Lennie
in Of Mice and Men.

1428
01:06:05,341 --> 01:06:07,116
What am I going to do,
kill it?

1429
01:06:07,176 --> 01:06:09,053
But, honey, look, it's over $3,000.
You don't want to--

1430
01:06:09,112 --> 01:06:10,523
Don't want to what?

1431
01:06:10,580 --> 01:06:11,820
All right.

1432
01:06:11,881 --> 01:06:13,292
Do what you want.

1433
01:06:13,349 --> 01:06:15,295
Hello, cutie.

1434
01:06:16,486 --> 01:06:18,193
Hi, cutie.

1435
01:06:18,254 --> 01:06:21,167
Aw, yes, honey.

1436
01:06:21,224 --> 01:06:22,897
My son's in town
just for a while.

1437
01:06:22,959 --> 01:06:24,438
That's why we're shopping today.

1438
01:06:27,563 --> 01:06:30,407
Normally he doesn't live with me.

1439
01:06:30,466 --> 01:06:32,571
He's divorced.

1440
01:06:32,635 --> 01:06:36,549
Actually, it's his second divorce.

1441
01:06:38,074 --> 01:06:42,079
They just can't seem
to stay married anymore.

1442
01:06:42,145 --> 01:06:44,147
I don't know.

1443
01:06:45,448 --> 01:06:47,928
I can't believe that you
told him I was divorced.

1444
01:06:47,984 --> 01:06:49,292
Honey, he asked.

1445
01:06:49,352 --> 01:06:52,094
Oh, I'm sure he did.
That's what they do in these stores.

1446
01:06:52,155 --> 01:06:53,930
Before they can sell you a bird,

1447
01:06:53,990 --> 01:06:55,594
they need to know
your marital status.

1448
01:06:55,658 --> 01:06:56,898
What difference does it make?

1449
01:06:56,959 --> 01:06:59,098
What if we were man and wife?

1450
01:06:59,162 --> 01:07:00,732
Shh! Honey, please!

1451
01:07:00,797 --> 01:07:03,607
Oh, Mother, I got to run
in here for one second.

1452
01:07:03,666 --> 01:07:06,670
I got to get a woman
something very quickly.

1453
01:07:06,736 --> 01:07:08,044
What, what?

1454
01:07:08,104 --> 01:07:10,380
You're going to get a woman
something in here?

1455
01:07:10,440 --> 01:07:11,384
Yeah.

1456
01:07:11,441 --> 01:07:12,715
Who?

1457
01:07:24,220 --> 01:07:25,722
Excuse me?

1458
01:07:25,788 --> 01:07:27,768
Welcome to Victoria's Secret.
May I help you?

1459
01:07:27,824 --> 01:07:30,202
Yes, I'm buying my mother
a pair of crotchless panties.

1460
01:07:30,259 --> 01:07:31,431
You're what?

1461
01:07:31,494 --> 01:07:33,770
Wonderful. Do you know
what size you are, ma'am?

1462
01:07:33,830 --> 01:07:34,968
What size are you?

1463
01:07:35,031 --> 01:07:37,807
Uh, n-n-n-I'm--
No size. No--

1464
01:07:37,867 --> 01:07:40,177
He's just joking.
He's a writer.

1465
01:07:40,236 --> 01:07:41,772
It's all made up.
We're not getting anything.

1466
01:07:41,838 --> 01:07:44,079
We're getting out of here.
Thank you.

1467
01:07:44,140 --> 01:07:45,585
She's shy. Sexy, but shy.

1468
01:07:45,641 --> 01:07:47,245
It's an experiment, you see?

1469
01:07:47,310 --> 01:07:50,120
I'm part of an experiment...

1470
01:07:50,179 --> 01:07:52,853
Where we're things
that we're not.

1471
01:08:01,090 --> 01:08:03,297
Remind me to call Jeff
when I get home.

1472
01:08:03,359 --> 01:08:05,430
That's now the 30th time
you told me that.

1473
01:08:05,495 --> 01:08:06,872
I don't want to forget.

1474
01:08:06,929 --> 01:08:09,375
What are you so worried about?
What if you forgot?

1475
01:08:09,432 --> 01:08:11,036
That has nothing
to do with it.

1476
01:08:11,100 --> 01:08:13,011
You know they want me
to come down there,

1477
01:08:13,069 --> 01:08:14,810
and they need to know
about the room.

1478
01:08:14,871 --> 01:08:16,214
Come down there? When?

1479
01:08:16,272 --> 01:08:17,945
I was going to go this weekend.

1480
01:08:18,007 --> 01:08:19,042
But I'm here.

1481
01:08:19,108 --> 01:08:20,678
You want to come with me?

1482
01:08:20,743 --> 01:08:22,484
No. I just came from there.

1483
01:08:22,545 --> 01:08:24,684
Mother, we need time alone.

1484
01:08:24,747 --> 01:08:26,055
We do?

1485
01:08:26,115 --> 01:08:28,220
Look, I don't want
to upset your life.

1486
01:08:28,284 --> 01:08:30,059
You do what you want to do.

1487
01:08:30,119 --> 01:08:31,894
You don't want to upset my life?

1488
01:08:31,954 --> 01:08:33,627
I thought that was part
of the experiment.

1489
01:08:33,689 --> 01:08:36,067
No, it's not part
of the experiment.

1490
01:08:36,125 --> 01:08:37,570
Go visit Jeff.

1491
01:08:37,627 --> 01:08:39,573
No. I'll stay with you.

1492
01:08:39,629 --> 01:08:42,542
Are you sure that's
what you want to do?

1493
01:08:42,598 --> 01:08:46,239
No, dear, I'm not,
but I'll stay.

1494
01:08:48,304 --> 01:08:51,148
Well, Christ, Mom,
we're all expecting you.

1495
01:08:51,207 --> 01:08:52,914
You can't just do that.

1496
01:08:52,975 --> 01:08:54,977
Well, it's just that John is here.

1497
01:08:55,044 --> 01:08:56,751
And let me get through with him,

1498
01:08:56,812 --> 01:08:58,314
and then I'll come down there.

1499
01:08:58,381 --> 01:09:00,088
But how long will that be?

1500
01:09:00,149 --> 01:09:01,594
I don't know, honey.

1501
01:09:01,651 --> 01:09:03,096
He doesn't tell me.

1502
01:09:03,152 --> 01:09:04,995
What's going on?

1503
01:09:05,054 --> 01:09:06,397
That's great.

1504
01:09:06,455 --> 01:09:08,731
You know, somebody could have
told us before, Mother.

1505
01:09:08,791 --> 01:09:09,735
We had plans.

1506
01:09:09,792 --> 01:09:12,033
What's the problem?

1507
01:09:12,094 --> 01:09:14,074
I should be asking you that.

1508
01:09:14,130 --> 01:09:16,201
We are planned.
Now she's not coming.

1509
01:09:16,265 --> 01:09:17,437
You know what?

1510
01:09:17,500 --> 01:09:19,502
You talk to her
every goddamned day of your life.

1511
01:09:19,569 --> 01:09:21,071
Can I have this
little bit of time?

1512
01:09:21,137 --> 01:09:23,879
I don't talk to her every
goddamned day of anybody's life,

1513
01:09:23,940 --> 01:09:26,045
and you can do whatever you want.

1514
01:09:26,108 --> 01:09:28,384
Get some help, buddy!

1515
01:09:29,645 --> 01:09:31,215
Hey!

1516
01:09:46,462 --> 01:09:48,601
Watch it, will you?

1517
01:09:49,799 --> 01:09:51,574
What's the matter with you?

1518
01:09:51,634 --> 01:09:53,636
My mother's not coming here
this weekend.

1519
01:09:53,703 --> 01:09:54,909
Where's she going?

1520
01:09:54,971 --> 01:09:56,746
She's staying
up there with John.

1521
01:09:56,806 --> 01:09:58,410
So that's OK, isn't it?

1522
01:09:58,474 --> 01:10:00,283
We had a plan, didn't we?

1523
01:10:00,343 --> 01:10:02,186
She was going to come down here.

1524
01:10:02,244 --> 01:10:04,246
We were going to do something
with the kids. Yes?

1525
01:10:04,313 --> 01:10:06,919
Yes. We can't do something
with the kids?

1526
01:10:06,983 --> 01:10:08,394
That's not the point.

1527
01:10:08,451 --> 01:10:10,192
No, that is the point.

1528
01:10:10,252 --> 01:10:12,254
It's almost like
you're not going to live

1529
01:10:12,321 --> 01:10:13,629
unless your mother comes here.

1530
01:10:13,689 --> 01:10:15,430
I like to be with my mother.

1531
01:10:15,491 --> 01:10:17,198
Is there something wrong
with that?

1532
01:10:17,259 --> 01:10:19,034
I mean, just because
I get along with mine.

1533
01:10:19,095 --> 01:10:20,438
Oh, go to hell.

1534
01:10:20,496 --> 01:10:22,806
I'm tired of this,
and there's a big difference

1535
01:10:22,865 --> 01:10:25,539
between getting along with
and not being able to live without.

1536
01:10:25,601 --> 01:10:26,875
What does that mean?

1537
01:10:26,936 --> 01:10:28,711
It means you're a mama's boy.

1538
01:10:28,771 --> 01:10:30,250
Screw you!

1539
01:10:32,141 --> 01:10:33,848
I'm not a mama's boy.

1540
01:10:33,909 --> 01:10:35,547
I love my mother.

1541
01:10:35,611 --> 01:10:37,557
What's wrong with that?

1542
01:10:37,613 --> 01:10:40,184
How do you think
that makes me feel?

1543
01:10:40,249 --> 01:10:42,559
You find out that your mother's
not coming here,

1544
01:10:42,618 --> 01:10:44,063
and your world ends.

