I mean, oh.

1799
01:20:25,901 --> 01:20:28,177
Oh, hello.

1800
01:20:28,237 --> 01:20:29,875
You must be Charles.

1801
01:20:29,938 --> 01:20:31,884
You must be the other son.

1802
01:20:31,940 --> 01:20:33,544
Are you still blocked?

1803
01:20:33,609 --> 01:20:34,713
Still blocked?

1804
01:20:34,776 --> 01:20:36,380
Yeah.
Word travels, doesn't it?

1805
01:20:36,445 --> 01:20:38,083
I've heard an awful lot
about you.

1806
01:20:38,146 --> 01:20:39,887
Your mother's very proud of you.

1807
01:20:39,948 --> 01:20:41,894
I thought you had
the wrong address.

1808
01:20:41,950 --> 01:20:43,224
Now I'm positive.

1809
01:20:43,285 --> 01:20:45,060
You should hear her
talk about you.

1810
01:20:45,120 --> 01:20:46,565
I have.
That's why I'm here.

1811
01:20:46,622 --> 01:20:48,568
When you're not here,
she brags her head off.

1812
01:20:48,624 --> 01:20:49,932
What does she do?

1813
01:20:49,992 --> 01:20:53,064
Marvel that I can get all
of my fat under my clothes?

1814
01:20:53,128 --> 01:20:55,130
No, I haven't heard that one.
How do you do that?

1815
01:20:55,197 --> 01:20:56,574
Oh, there she is.

1816
01:20:56,632 --> 01:20:57,906
I see you've met.

1817
01:20:57,966 --> 01:20:59,912
What are you two talking about?

1818
01:20:59,968 --> 01:21:02,244
Just the whole damn thing,
that's all.

1819
01:21:02,304 --> 01:21:04,580
Honey, don't
bother him with the experiment.

1820
01:21:04,640 --> 01:21:05,584
He'll never understand.

1821
01:21:05,641 --> 01:21:07,143
I didn't say anything.

1822
01:21:07,209 --> 01:21:08,688
He's not like us.

1823
01:21:08,744 --> 01:21:10,246
I didn't tell anything.

1824
01:21:10,312 --> 01:21:13,054
All right, I'm ready to go.

1825
01:21:13,115 --> 01:21:15,288
Honey, there's some food
in the refrigerator.

1826
01:21:15,350 --> 01:21:17,352
Mother, you promised.
No more food talk.

1827
01:21:17,419 --> 01:21:19,524
All right, dear.

1828
01:21:21,089 --> 01:21:24,366
Be asleep when we get home.

1829
01:21:25,927 --> 01:21:28,533
You have that food problem, too?

1830
01:21:40,609 --> 01:21:43,556
So he didn't want to
stay in a hotel.

1831
01:21:43,612 --> 01:21:45,888
Let's not let that
ruin our evening.

1832
01:21:45,947 --> 01:21:47,551
Oh, it's not ruining anything.

1833
01:21:47,616 --> 01:21:51,063
By the way,
for later on, I, uh...

1834
01:21:51,119 --> 01:21:53,065
I rented that movie.

1835
01:21:53,121 --> 01:21:55,567
Oh, we're not watching any movies.
No, no, no.

1836
01:21:55,624 --> 01:21:57,228
You'll just drop me off.

1837
01:21:57,292 --> 01:21:58,566
What?

1838
01:21:58,627 --> 01:22:00,573
This is not the time for that.

1839
01:22:00,629 --> 01:22:03,075
When he goes back to Los Angeles,
you'll show me.

1840
01:22:03,131 --> 01:22:05,236
I don't want to wait that long.

1841
01:22:05,300 --> 01:22:06,574
When is he going back?

1842
01:22:06,635 --> 01:22:08,342
I don't know, but no movies--
not tonight.

1843
01:22:08,403 --> 01:22:09,507
Now, please.

1844
01:22:09,571 --> 01:22:11,517
Beatrice, I'm sorry,
but I don't understand.

1845
01:22:11,573 --> 01:22:12,847
Well, think about it.

1846
01:22:12,908 --> 01:22:16,014
I have a 40-year-old man
20 feet away,

1847
01:22:16,078 --> 01:22:18,684
and I don't feel very private.

1848
01:22:18,747 --> 01:22:21,523
Wasn't that
one of your fantasies?

1849
01:22:21,583 --> 01:22:26,191
A 40-year-old man...
20 feet away...

1850
01:22:26,254 --> 01:22:29,531
No. That was a 60-year-old man
6 feet under.

1851
01:22:29,591 --> 01:22:31,696
Now I'm warning you,
he's my son,

1852
01:22:31,760 --> 01:22:34,206
and I don't want
to talk about it.

1853
01:22:34,262 --> 01:22:35,366
All right.

1854
01:22:35,430 --> 01:22:37,376
Let's just have a nice dinner,

1855
01:22:37,432 --> 01:22:39,207
and then maybe later
you'll change your mind.

1856
01:22:39,267 --> 01:22:40,712
I'm not going to change my mind.

1857
01:22:40,769 --> 01:22:43,215
No movies, no nothing,
until he goes home.

1858
01:22:43,271 --> 01:22:46,047
Well, we can talk about it
in the car, can't we?

1859
01:22:46,108 --> 01:22:48,054
That's a silly place
to talk about it.

1860
01:22:48,110 --> 01:22:51,387
God forbid,
what if we got pulled over?

1861
01:22:51,446 --> 01:22:54,893
I think you're thinking
of dirty underwear.

1862
01:22:54,950 --> 01:22:57,226
They don't know what
you're talking about.

1863
01:22:57,285 --> 01:22:59,561
Oh, don't be too sure.

1864
01:22:59,621 --> 01:23:01,897
When they point
those things at you,

1865
01:23:01,957 --> 01:23:04,403
I just wonder
what they really know.

1866
01:23:15,504 --> 01:23:17,074
<i>...beef jerky,</i>

1867
01:23:17,139 --> 01:23:20,086
<i>just marinate in a combination
of soy sauce and brown sugar.</i>

1868
01:23:20,142 --> 01:23:22,918
<i>Place the meat on the trays,
you plug it in,</i>

1869
01:23:22,978 --> 01:23:26,892
<i>and that's all there is
to making beef jerky.</i>

1870
01:23:26,948 --> 01:23:28,928
<i>I learned technique.</i>

1871
01:23:28,984 --> 01:23:31,260
<i>That's why I wrote
the Warner book, Technique.</i>

1872
01:23:31,319 --> 01:23:33,265
<i>Take a look at Paul Avaloni.</i>

1873
01:23:33,321 --> 01:23:35,267
<i>Look at him-- 60-inch waist.</i>

1874
01:23:35,323 --> 01:23:38,099
<i>Look at this.
That's what we're talking about.</i>

1875
01:23:38,160 --> 01:23:39,798
<i>Right?</i>

1876
01:23:39,861 --> 01:23:42,603
<i>Look at this. Really fine.</i>

1877
01:23:42,664 --> 01:23:44,575
<i>This is perfect.</i>

1878
01:23:44,633 --> 01:23:46,112
<i>So many recipes
call for chopped onion.</i>

1879
01:23:46,168 --> 01:23:47,613
<i>That's right,
and Mexican food--</i>

1880
01:23:47,669 --> 01:23:49,148
<i>Oh, I love Mexican food.</i>

1881
01:23:49,204 --> 01:23:51,946
<i>But watch how it works, ladies.</i>

1882
01:23:52,007 --> 01:23:53,611
<i>We're ready. This is great.</i>

1883
01:23:53,675 --> 01:23:55,586
<i>We've seen this once.</i>

1884
01:23:55,644 --> 01:23:57,624
<i>Look at the smile on Ari's face.</i>

1885
01:23:57,679 --> 01:23:59,625
<i>Now, Ron, you're about
3 inches from his scalp--</i>

1886
01:23:59,681 --> 01:24:01,126
<i>That's all you do.</i>

1887
01:24:01,183 --> 01:24:02,457
<i>And you're just spraying it,</i>

1888
01:24:02,517 --> 01:24:04,463
<i>like you would
a bottle of hairspray.</i>

1889
01:24:04,519 --> 01:24:05,827
<i>It's as simple as that.</i>

1890
01:25:24,799 --> 01:25:27,803
"Jeanette's Secret Locket"

1891
01:25:44,653 --> 01:25:47,099
"As I turned the corner
on main street,

1892
01:25:47,155 --> 01:25:50,432
the sun was shining
right behind me."

1893
01:25:54,162 --> 01:25:56,506
"Princess Anna"

1894
01:26:05,006 --> 01:26:07,885
"Irene Takes a Lover"

1895
01:26:14,282 --> 01:26:16,888
"The room was dark
except for the slash of light

1896
01:26:16,952 --> 01:26:18,454
that peeked through the curtains.

1897
01:26:18,520 --> 01:26:22,058
Irene dreaded going home.

1898
01:26:22,123 --> 01:26:23,727
The darkness of the house

1899
01:26:23,792 --> 01:26:25,794
equaled the darkness
of her marriage."

1900
01:26:25,860 --> 01:26:28,067
This looks good.

1901
01:26:28,129 --> 01:26:30,575
Unbelievable.

1902
01:26:38,640 --> 01:26:41,416
Ha ha ha!

1903
01:27:08,103 --> 01:27:09,207
Please?

1904
01:27:09,270 --> 01:27:10,374
Shh.

1905
01:27:10,438 --> 01:27:12,042
No, I'm just saying please.

1906
01:27:12,107 --> 01:27:13,381
Don't beg-- not here.

1907
01:27:13,441 --> 01:27:14,715
What if he's asleep already?

1908
01:27:14,776 --> 01:27:16,221
You said he's
a very sound sleeper.

1909
01:27:16,277 --> 01:27:18,382
That's Jeff. I don't think
this one ever sleeps.

1910
01:27:18,446 --> 01:27:20,221
Why don't we just
go in and see,

1911
01:27:20,281 --> 01:27:22,056
and then if he's up,
I'll leave.

1912
01:27:22,117 --> 01:27:23,721
Well, all right.

1913
01:27:36,564 --> 01:27:37,565
John?

1914
01:27:37,632 --> 01:27:39,077
Oh, hi.

1915
01:27:39,134 --> 01:27:40,579
What are you doing?

1916
01:27:40,635 --> 01:27:42,080
What do you mean?

1917
01:27:42,137 --> 01:27:44,083
Why do you have
all this stuff out?

1918
01:27:44,139 --> 01:27:46,449
Well, I'm just looking at it.

1919
01:27:46,508 --> 01:27:48,579
Well, who told you
you could do that?

1920
01:27:48,643 --> 01:27:49,917
That's mine.

1921
01:27:49,978 --> 01:27:51,582
Who told you to do that?

1922
01:27:51,646 --> 01:27:54,092
What right have you got
to touch my stuff?

1923
01:27:54,149 --> 01:27:55,423
Mother, take it easy.

1924
01:27:55,483 --> 01:27:57,588
I just saw the boxes
in the closet.

1925
01:27:57,652 --> 01:27:59,757
Mother?

1926
01:28:01,656 --> 01:28:04,603
I'll call you later.
I need to talk to John.

1927
01:28:04,659 --> 01:28:06,605
Are you sure?
I thought maybe--

1928
01:28:06,661 --> 01:28:07,696
That's it.

1929
01:28:09,597 --> 01:28:10,701
Good night.

1930
01:28:12,600 --> 01:28:13,704
Good night.

1931
01:28:13,768 --> 01:28:14,872
Good night.

1932
01:28:21,109 --> 01:28:23,055
I am very upset with you,
really.

1933
01:28:23,111 --> 01:28:25,057
I don't rummage
through your stuff.

1934
01:28:25,113 --> 01:28:27,218
I didn't do anything.
What's the big deal?

1935
01:28:27,282 --> 01:28:29,057
What have you got to hide?

1936
01:28:29,117 --> 01:28:30,562
I have nothing to hide.

1937
01:28:30,618 --> 01:28:32,564
These boxes are put away
for a reason.

1938
01:28:32,620 --> 01:28:33,724
What reason?

1939
01:28:33,788 --> 01:28:35,062
My reason.

1940
01:28:35,123 --> 01:28:37,569
All right,
I'm putting it all away.

1941
01:28:39,794 --> 01:28:41,034
Mother...

1942
01:28:42,630 --> 01:28:43,734
Mother?

1943
01:28:52,140 --> 01:28:53,915
Did you write all that stuff?

1944
01:28:53,975 --> 01:28:55,750
No. A little elf wrote it.

1945
01:28:55,810 --> 01:28:57,414
Of course I wrote it.

1946
01:28:57,479 --> 01:28:59,425
You know, the children's story
was beautiful.

1947
01:28:59,481 --> 01:29:01,427
I'm not sure what
you're talking about.

1948
01:29:01,483 --> 01:29:03,087
I've written many of those,

1949
01:29:03,151 --> 01:29:04,755
and that was a long time ago.

1950
01:29:04,819 --> 01:29:06,264
And I'll tell you something--

1951
01:29:06,321 --> 01:29:08,858
If I thought people would
be rummaging through this,

1952
01:29:08,923 --> 01:29:10,698
I don't think
I would have saved anything.

1953
01:29:10,759 --> 01:29:13,706
What are you talking about, people?
I'm your goddamn son.

1954
01:29:13,762 --> 01:29:15,036
Please.

1955
01:29:15,096 --> 01:29:18,043
Oh, Mother, we're 7 walls away
from another ear.

1956
01:29:19,934 --> 01:29:21,880
What else did you look at?

1957
01:29:21,936 --> 01:29:24,212
I was just looking
through the boxes

1958
01:29:24,272 --> 01:29:26,411
and just seeing what was in them,
that's all.

1959
01:29:26,474 --> 01:29:29,045
That was another part of me.
That's the past.

1960
01:29:29,110 --> 01:29:30,555
You know I don't like
to look back.

1961
01:29:30,612 --> 01:29:31,886
Your father always said,

1962
01:29:31,946 --> 01:29:33,926
"Never look back.
They might be gaining on you."

1963
01:29:33,982 --> 01:29:36,087
I think it was Satchel Paige
who said that.

1964
01:29:37,786 --> 01:29:40,926
So when did you do all this stuff?

1965
01:29:40,989 --> 01:29:42,900
It was a long time ago.

1966
01:29:42,957 --> 01:29:44,561
You weren't even born then.

1967
01:29:44,626 --> 01:29:47,903
What are you doing?
You smoke?

1968
01:29:47,962 --> 01:29:50,067
I'll have one once a year

1969
01:29:50,131 --> 01:29:52,077
when I'm feeling this way.

1970
01:29:52,133 --> 01:29:54,909
Boy, you really must be upset.

1971
01:29:54,969 --> 01:29:57,575
Look, we're actually
using the living room.

1972
01:29:59,140 --> 01:30:01,086
I'm going to take
all those boxes out of there.

1973
01:30:01,142 --> 01:30:02,917
You can have the entire closet.

1974
01:30:02,977 --> 01:30:04,581
We'll do it in the morning.

1975
01:30:04,646 --> 01:30:06,592
You don't have to
take the boxes out.

1976
01:30:06,648 --> 01:30:08,685
If you ask me not to look at it,
I won't look at it.

1977
01:30:08,750 --> 01:30:10,354
I think it'll be safer.

1978
01:30:10,418 --> 01:30:13,524
Oh, safer, whatever.
Take them all out. I don't care.

1979
01:30:13,588 --> 01:30:15,192
Honey, do you remember once

1980
01:30:15,256 --> 01:30:17,202
when I looked at
your high-school yearbook

1981
01:30:17,258 --> 01:30:19,829
and how upset you were because
of the pictures you didn't like?

1982
01:30:19,894 --> 01:30:22,204
You weren't looking
at my high-school yearbook.

1983
01:30:22,263 --> 01:30:24,209
You were showing it to everyone.

1984
01:30:24,265 --> 01:30:26,040
That's what I remember.

1985
01:30:26,100 --> 01:30:28,376
"Look, everybody.
Doesn't his head look a little big?"

1986
01:30:28,436 --> 01:30:29,608
Remember?

1987
01:30:29,671 --> 01:30:32,151
Wait a second.

1988
01:30:32,207 --> 01:30:35,814
It just occurred to me.
This is why I write about big heads.

1989
01:30:35,877 --> 01:30:39,154
Oh, blame something else on me.

1990
01:30:39,214 --> 01:30:41,057
I'm not blaming anything on you.

1991
01:30:41,115 --> 01:30:42,890
I think that's
a very good character.

1992
01:30:42,951 --> 01:30:44,396
He's not a good character.

1993
01:30:44,452 --> 01:30:46,056
You want to know why?

1994
01:30:46,120 --> 01:30:47,224
Yes.

1995
01:30:47,288 --> 01:30:49,393
You make someone
with a head that big,

1996
01:30:49,457 --> 01:30:51,403
but he's stupider
than everyone else.

1997
01:30:51,459 --> 01:30:53,063
I was just trying
to be different.

1998
01:30:53,127 --> 01:30:55,505
Why can't a guy have a big head
and still be stupid?

1999
01:30:55,563 --> 01:30:57,406
Why is his head that big, then?

2000
01:30:57,465 --> 01:30:59,911
Well, part of it's empty.

2001
01:30:59,968 --> 01:31:01,914
Honey,
no God's going to create

2002
01:31:01,970 --> 01:31:04,576
a head that big
with nothing in it.

2003
01:31:04,639 --> 01:31:06,175
What about the dinosaurs?

2004
01:31:06,241 --> 01:31:07,413
Their heads were full.

2005
01:31:07,475 --> 01:31:09,011
They just had small heads.

2006
01:31:09,077 --> 01:31:12,684
You never saw a dinosaur
with a huge head and a little brain.

2007
01:31:12,747 --> 01:31:14,749
Their brain was the size
of their head.

2008
01:31:14,816 --> 01:31:17,194
I don't know how the hell
we got on this subject,

2009
01:31:17,252 --> 01:31:20,028
but you should see yourself
when you talk to me about this.

2010
01:31:20,088 --> 01:31:21,692
You just light up.

2011
01:31:21,756 --> 01:31:23,702
Boy, Mother, you must have stuffed

2012
01:31:23,758 --> 01:31:27,103
the creative part of you
way down there somewhere.

2013
01:31:27,161 --> 01:31:30,540
Oh, no. You're not going
to analyze me at midnight.

2014
01:31:56,958 --> 01:32:00,064
Which children's story
did you read?

2015
01:32:00,128 --> 01:32:03,473
The one about the flight
around the world.

2016
01:32:03,531 --> 01:32:06,239
That was about Amelia Earhart.

2017
01:32:06,301 --> 01:32:08,303
Do you remember her?

2018
01:32:08,369 --> 01:32:10,007
Yes, of course I do.

2019
01:32:10,071 --> 01:32:11,846
That was very clever,
what you did.

2020
01:32:11,906 --> 01:32:14,512
You took a real character,
but you turned it into fiction.

2021
01:32:14,575 --> 01:32:16,521
You know, that was
way ahead of your time.

2022
01:32:16,577 --> 01:32:18,147
Woodward and Bernstein did that.

2023
01:32:18,212 --> 01:32:20,749
I'm trying to think
of who that is.

2024
01:32:20,815 --> 01:32:22,658
It doesn't matter.
It's a compliment.

2025
01:32:22,717 --> 01:32:26,358
So tell me something-- where
did you learn all about this stuff?

2026
01:32:26,421 --> 01:32:28,697
Did you think
I was born yesterday?

2027
01:32:28,756 --> 01:32:31,032
You know, every child
thinks their mother

2028
01:32:31,092 --> 01:32:33,868
just came to life
when they were born.

2029
01:32:33,928 --> 01:32:36,670
I was around
a long time before you.

2030
01:32:36,731 --> 01:32:38,540
Well, that's the part
I'm trying to find out.

2031
01:32:38,599 --> 01:32:41,239
Every time I ask a question, you
don't seem to want to talk about it.

2032
01:32:41,302 --> 01:32:42,406
Well, it's in the past.

2033
01:32:42,470 --> 01:32:45,713
Stop saying that, Mother.
It's not in the past.

2034
01:32:45,773 --> 01:32:48,811
That past is plopped
all over our lives.

2035
01:32:48,876 --> 01:32:50,549
How much have you written?

2036
01:32:50,611 --> 01:32:52,557
Did you ever get
anything published?

2037
01:32:52,613 --> 01:32:54,058
No, I never published.

2038
01:32:54,115 --> 01:32:56,117
Your father talked me out of it.

2039
01:32:56,184 --> 01:32:57,993
Why would he do that?

2040
01:32:58,052 --> 01:33:01,966
Well, you know, dear, in those days
a woman didn't have a career.

2041
01:33:02,023 --> 01:33:04,060
You know, she just...

2042
01:33:04,125 --> 01:33:07,572
Raised children who she hated
for ruining her life

2043
01:33:07,628 --> 01:33:11,735
and killing her chances at doing
the one thing she loved.

2044
01:33:14,802 --> 01:33:16,247
Well, my goodness.

2045
01:33:16,304 --> 01:33:20,081
I never heard it put
exactly like that,

2046
01:33:20,141 --> 01:33:22,087
but...yes...

2047
01:33:22,143 --> 01:33:25,090
I'm afraid that's true.

2048
01:33:25,146 --> 01:33:27,251
We did it.

2049
01:33:27,315 --> 01:33:29,727
We figured it out, Mother.

2050
01:33:29,784 --> 01:33:31,923
Look what just happened.

2051
01:33:31,986 --> 01:33:34,364
We know why you hate me.

2052
01:33:34,422 --> 01:33:36,868
We know why she hates me!

2053
01:33:36,924 --> 01:33:39,666
We know why she hates me...

2054
01:33:39,705 --> 01:33:41,905
We know why she hates me...

2055
01:33:42,063 --> 01:33:44,100
I don't hate you.
Stop it!

2056
01:33:44,165 --> 01:33:45,701
Sit down!

2057
01:33:45,767 --> 01:33:47,940
Mother, this is so exciting!

2058
01:33:48,002 --> 01:33:49,379
I want to hear everything.

2059
01:33:49,437 --> 01:33:51,610
Tell me exactly,
when did you start to write?

2060
01:33:51,672 --> 01:33:53,276
I started in high school,

2061
01:33:53,341 --> 01:33:55,446
and then I got
a scholarship to college.

2062
01:33:55,510 --> 01:33:56,784
Because of the writing?

2063
01:33:56,844 --> 01:33:58,448
Yes. That's where I met
your father, in college.

2064
01:33:58,513 --> 01:33:59,651
You know that.

2065
01:33:59,714 --> 01:34:01,625
Yeah, but I never knew
how you got there.

2066
01:34:01,682 --> 01:34:03,662
No kid knows what
his parents majored in.

2067
01:34:03,718 --> 01:34:05,197
I never told you, huh?

2068
01:34:05,253 --> 01:34:07,563
So no wonder
you like Jeff better.

2069
01:34:07,622 --> 01:34:08,896
There's no threat there.

2070
01:34:08,956 --> 01:34:11,095
I just have to be
a huge threat to you.

2071
01:34:11,159 --> 01:34:13,070
I don't like Jeff better.

2072
01:34:13,127 --> 01:34:15,403
But still, he doesn't
represent the writer.

2073
01:34:15,463 --> 01:34:18,410
I represent
what you had to stop.

2074
01:34:20,134 --> 01:34:21,909
Maybe you're right.

2075
01:34:21,969 --> 01:34:23,949
How do you like that?

2076
01:34:24,005 --> 01:34:25,746
Listen to me.

2077
01:34:25,807 --> 01:34:27,582
I'm sorry, Mother.

2078
01:34:27,642 --> 01:34:30,748
I wish I could have done something
to change all of this--

2079
01:34:30,812 --> 01:34:31,916
you know that--

2080
01:34:31,979 --> 01:34:33,925
but I had nothing
to do with it.

2081
01:34:33,981 --> 01:34:37,588
But for the very first time,
for the first time,

2082
01:34:37,652 --> 01:34:41,122
I don't see you as my mother.

2083
01:34:41,189 --> 01:34:44,602
I see you as a failure...

2084
01:34:44,659 --> 01:34:46,969
And it's wonderful.

2085
01:34:47,028 --> 01:34:50,271
I'm a failure,
and that's wonderful?

2086
01:34:52,333 --> 01:34:54,108
All right, honey...

2087
01:34:54,168 --> 01:34:56,774
If that's what you need.

2088
01:35:12,787 --> 01:35:15,734
Mother, I'm going into town
for a little bit.

2089
01:35:15,790 --> 01:35:17,064
I'll be back later.

2090
01:35:17,125 --> 01:35:19,571
Oh, honey, listen.
I was thinking this morning.

2091
01:35:19,627 --> 01:35:22,073
As long as you have
your computer in there,

2092
01:35:22,130 --> 01:35:24,576
I don't think one phone line
is enough.

2093
01:35:24,632 --> 01:35:27,078
So go ahead and get
the other phone line

2094
01:35:27,135 --> 01:35:29,081
that you wanted
just for the computer.

2095
01:35:29,137 --> 01:35:31,083
Thanks, but I don't need it.

2096
01:35:31,139 --> 01:35:32,243
Why?

2097
01:35:32,306 --> 01:35:34,411
Because we're through.

2098
01:35:34,475 --> 01:35:35,579
We did it.

2099
01:35:35,643 --> 01:35:36,917
We did?

2100
01:35:36,978 --> 01:35:39,083
Mother, I came here
not understanding anything,

2101
01:35:39,147 --> 01:35:41,423
and now I understand all of it.

2102
01:35:41,482 --> 01:35:43,758
So just live your life, OK?

2103
01:35:43,818 --> 01:35:47,095
Live your life,
and I'll do the best I can.

2104
01:35:47,155 --> 01:35:49,431
I don't blame you
for anything anymore.

2105
01:35:49,490 --> 01:35:50,764
It's not your fault.

2106
01:35:50,825 --> 01:35:52,805
I see you as a real person.

2107
01:35:52,860 --> 01:35:54,100
You do?

2108
01:35:54,162 --> 01:35:56,267
Yes, and it's fine.

2109
01:35:56,330 --> 01:35:59,106
My goodness. I didn't get
that moment that you did.

2110
01:35:59,167 --> 01:36:00,612
You will. Don't worry.

2111
01:36:00,668 --> 01:36:02,944
So you don't need to stay, then?

2112
01:36:03,004 --> 01:36:04,312
No. I'm fine.

2113
01:36:04,372 --> 01:36:06,613
Go down to LA.
Stay with Jeff.

2114
01:36:06,674 --> 01:36:08,881
Sleep with Charles.
Do whatever you want.

2115
01:36:08,943 --> 01:36:10,286
Oh...

2116
01:36:10,344 --> 01:36:11,721
But, Mother, just think.

2117
01:36:11,779 --> 01:36:13,554
From now on,
when we talk on the phone,

2118
01:36:13,614 --> 01:36:15,890
we don't talk
as mother and son.

2119
01:36:15,950 --> 01:36:17,554
We talk like 2 writers.

2120
01:36:17,618 --> 01:36:19,564
One blocked and insecure,

2121
01:36:19,620 --> 01:36:21,531
One stifled and angry.

2122
01:36:21,589 --> 01:36:25,127
Which one am I, dear?
I forget.

2123
01:36:28,129 --> 01:36:31,008
So, are you going to
go back to work now?

2124
01:36:31,065 --> 01:36:33,909
No. I think I'm going to
take a couple of weeks off

2125
01:36:33,968 --> 01:36:35,572
and just enjoy this realization.

2126
01:36:35,636 --> 01:36:37,479
Maybe I'll even buy myself
some new clothes.

2127
01:36:37,538 --> 01:36:39,575
That's what I like to hear.

2128
01:36:39,640 --> 01:36:42,018
Do buy yourself some new clothes.

2129
01:36:42,076 --> 01:36:44,249
All right,
I'll make you a deal.

2130
01:36:44,312 --> 01:36:46,588
For every new piece
of clothing I buy,

2131
01:36:46,647 --> 01:36:48,593
you buy one brand-new ounce

2132
01:36:48,649 --> 01:36:50,253
of very expensive cheese.

2133
01:36:51,819 --> 01:36:53,560
Does Kraft count?

2134
01:36:53,621 --> 01:36:58,092
Oh, Mother, that's so sweet.

2135
01:36:58,159 --> 01:37:01,766
Yes. Yes, Kraft counts.

2136
01:37:04,732 --> 01:37:06,109
I'll miss you.

2137
01:37:06,167 --> 01:37:07,942
I'll miss you, too, Mother.

2138
01:37:08,002 --> 01:37:10,039
Bye. Love you.

2139
01:37:10,104 --> 01:37:12,550
If it gets cold,
put the top up.

2140
01:37:44,305 --> 01:37:45,784
Oh, my God.

2141
01:37:45,840 --> 01:37:48,411
John Henderson?

2142
01:37:50,645 --> 01:37:52,386
Yes?

2143
01:37:52,446 --> 01:37:57,259
Planet 7 was the best book
I've ever read.

2144
01:37:57,318 --> 01:37:59,594
What did you say?

2145
01:37:59,654 --> 01:38:02,601
Planet 7 was the best book
I've ever read.

2146
01:38:02,657 --> 01:38:04,432
You're kidding me.

2147
01:38:04,492 --> 01:38:07,268
Why would I kid you?
My God, what about Planet 8?

2148
01:38:07,328 --> 01:38:08,773
I loved that one, too.

2149
01:38:08,829 --> 01:38:10,831
You read Planet 8?

2150
01:38:10,898 --> 01:38:13,435
Yeah, and I read
The Day There Was No Earth twice.

2151
01:38:13,501 --> 01:38:14,707
Twice?

2152
01:38:14,769 --> 01:38:15,873
Mm-hmm.

2153
01:38:15,936 --> 01:38:18,883
Did you like the character
with the big hand?

2154
01:38:18,939 --> 01:38:20,543
I loved that character.

2155
01:38:20,608 --> 01:38:22,246
Are you married?

2156
01:38:24,278 --> 01:38:26,224
No, I'm not married.

2157
01:38:26,280 --> 01:38:27,884
So, where do you live?

2158
01:38:27,948 --> 01:38:29,018
In Los Angeles.

2159
01:38:29,083 --> 01:38:30,562
Well, me, too.

2160
01:38:30,618 --> 01:38:32,222
Why don't you follow me,

2161
01:38:32,286 --> 01:38:34,061
and we'll stop along the way

2162
01:38:34,121 --> 01:38:36,727
and talk and eat
and get to know each other.

2163
01:38:36,791 --> 01:38:38,566
By the time we get there,

2164
01:38:38,626 --> 01:38:40,196
it'll be like 5 dates.

2165
01:38:41,629 --> 01:38:44,075
God, that's so creative.

2166
01:38:44,131 --> 01:38:45,576
Um...

2167
01:38:45,633 --> 01:38:48,546
Well, yeah,
that sounds wonderful.

2168
01:38:48,602 --> 01:38:50,548
That's a yes?

2169
01:38:50,604 --> 01:38:53,016
That's a yes.

2170
01:38:53,074 --> 01:38:54,246
Great.

2171
01:38:54,308 --> 01:38:56,584
This isn't a practical joke,
is it?

2172
01:38:56,644 --> 01:39:00,751
Nobody sent you here,
like my brother or somebody.

2173
01:39:00,815 --> 01:39:02,658
What are you talking about?

2174
01:39:02,717 --> 01:39:04,754
Nothing. It's just
this liking me stuff

2175
01:39:04,819 --> 01:39:06,594
is all virgin territory,
that's all.

2176
01:39:06,654 --> 01:39:08,065
I'm not used to it.

2177
01:39:08,122 --> 01:39:10,295
I'll get used to it.

2178
01:39:10,358 --> 01:39:12,031
You'll help me.

2179
01:39:12,093 --> 01:39:14,539
You read the whole book...

2180
01:39:16,097 --> 01:39:17,542
OK, so follow me.

2181
01:39:17,598 --> 01:39:19,043
Follow you.

2182
01:40:06,280 --> 01:40:08,692
Hello?

2183
01:40:08,749 --> 01:40:11,855
Oh, honey, I'm working.
May I call you back?

2184
01:40:11,920 --> 01:40:13,695
Bye.

